  "description": "<div style=\"width:800px;max-width:100%;margin:0 auto;padding:24px;font-family:-apple-system , BlinkMacSystemFont , 'Segoe UI' , Roboto , Helvetica , Arial , sans-serif;background-color:#ffffff;\">    <table width=\"100%\" style=\"background-color:#ffffff;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;border-radius:14px;overflow:hidden;\">        <tbody>\n<tr>      <td style=\"padding:28px 28px 22px 28px;background-color:#0b1020;background-image:linear-gradient(135deg,#0b1020 0%,#111b35 60%,#0b1020 100%);\">        <div style=\"font-size:30px;font-weight:750;color:#f8fafc;line-height:1.18;margin:0 0 10px 0;\">          Maxon Cinema 4D File Import-Export (<span style=\"color:#d6a44a;\">.C4D File</span>)        </div>        <div style=\"font-size:13px;color:rgba(248,250,252,0.78);margin:0 0 14px 0;line-height:1.6;\">          The fastest way to import Cinema 4D projects into Blender！        </div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:rgba(248,250,252,0.86);margin:0 0 14px 0;line-height:1.75;\">          A polished, production-ready addon that imports selected          <code style=\"background-color:rgba(248,250,252,0.10);border:1px solid rgba(248,250,252,0.14);padding:2px 6px;border-radius:6px;font-family:ui-monospace , SFMono-Regular , Menlo , Monaco , Consolas , monospace;color:#f8fafc;\">.c4d</code>          project files directly from Blender—no need to keep Cinema 4D open. It preserves core assets with minimal friction:        </div>        <table width=\"100%\" style=\"margin:0 0 14px 0;background-color:rgba(15,23,42,0.6);border-radius:8px;padding:15px;\">          <tbody>\n<tr>            <td style=\"padding-left:15px;font-size:14px;color:rgba(248,250,252,0.86);line-height:1.9;\">              <div style=\"margin-bottom:10px;\">                <strong style=\"color:#d6a44a;\">Animations</strong>: Transfer keyframed or procedural animations with precision.              </div>              <div style=\"margin-bottom:10px;\">                <strong style=\"color:#d6a44a;\">3D Models</strong>: Import geometry with full fidelity, ensuring smooth transitions between platforms.              </div>              <div style=\"margin-bottom:10px;\">                <strong style=\"color:#d6a44a;\">Materials</strong>: Support for standard materials as well as Redshift (RS) materials for advanced rendering workflows.              </div>              <div style=\"margin-bottom:10px;\">                <strong style=\"color:#d6a44a;\">Characters</strong>: Integrate rigged characters with associated assets for further editing or rendering in Blender.              </div>              <div style=\"margin-bottom:0;\">                <strong style=\"color:#d6a44a;\">Splines and Curves</strong>: Import splines for modeling, motion graphics, or animation use cases.              </div>            </td>          </tr>        </tbody>\n</table>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:rgba(248,250,252,0.86);margin:0 0 14px 0;line-height:1.75;\">          This addon is designed to enhance productivity for artists and studios working across both Cinema 4D and Blender, reducing the need for intermediate steps and maintaining the integrity of your creative work.        </div>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:15px;color:#000000;margin:0 0 8px 0;line-height:1.6;\">          <strong style=\"color:#000000;\">A revolutionary breakthrough! No need to install Cinema 4D now, you can use it directly!</strong>        </div>        <div style=\"font-size:15px;color:#000000;margin:0 0 8px 0;line-height:1.6;\">          <strong style=\"color:#000000;\">Now supported on macOS!</strong> The addon can run directly from Blender—Cinema 4D installation is no longer required.        </div>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">                <br>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tb