und-color:#f8fafc;margin:0 0 12px 0;\">            No. The addon runs inside Blender without requiring Cinema 4D to be running or installed. On macOS, a valid Maxon license is still required due to Apple’s policy.          </div>          <div style=\"font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:14px 0 6px 0;\">Does it work on both Windows and macOS?</div>          <div style=\"padding:10px 12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;border-radius:12px;background-color:#f8fafc;margin:0 0 12px 0;\">            Yes. It supports both Windows and macOS. macOS requires a Maxon license; Windows does <strong>not</strong>.          </div>          <div style=\"font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:14px 0 6px 0;\">Which Blender versions are supported?</div>          <div style=\"padding:10px 12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;border-radius:12px;background-color:#f8fafc;margin:0 0 12px 0;\">            Tested and officially supported on Blender <strong>4.2 – 5.0</strong>. Future updates may extend compatibility.          </div>          <div style=\"font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:14px 0 6px 0;\">What assets can I import from C4D?</div>          <div style=\"padding:10px 12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;border-radius:12px;background-color:#f8fafc;margin:0;\">            Animations (keyframed & procedural), 3D models, standard & Redshift materials, rigged characters with associated assets, plus splines and curves.          </div>        </div>      </td>    </tr>          <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Pricing</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 10px 0;\">Simple, artist-friendly pricing</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;margin:0 0 18px 0;line-height:1.75;\">          Buy once, use forever. Upgrade anytime if you need advanced import/export capabilities.        </div>        <div style=\"border:1px solid #e5e7eb;border-radius:14px;padding:18px;background-color:#f8fafc;\">          <div style=\"font-size:34px;font-weight:800;color:#0f172a;line-height:1;margin:0 0 6px 0;\">            $12 <span style=\"font-size:12px;font-weight:650;color:#475569;\">Standard Version</span>          </div>          <div style=\"font-size:13px;color:#475569;margin:0 0 12px 0;line-height:1.7;\">            Direct Blender import of <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;\">.c4d</strong> projects with support for animations, models, materials, characters and splines.          </div>          <div style=\"font-size:13px;color:#475569;margin:0 0 16px 0;line-height:1.75;\">            • <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;\">200+ sales</strong> on Superhive / Blendermarket<br>            • Trusted by artists working across Blender and Cinema 4D          </div>          <table width=\"100%\">            <tbody>\n<tr>              <td style=\"padding:0;\">                <a href=\"https://superhivemarket.com/products/maxon-cinema-4d-import-export-pro\" style=\"display:inline-block;padding:11px 18px;background-color:#ffffff;border:1px solid #cbd5e1;color:#0f172a;text-decoration:none;font-weight:650;font-size:14px;border-radius:999px;margin:0 10px 10px 0;\">                  View Pro Version ⤴                </a>                <a href=\"https://superhivemarket.com/products/maxon-cinema-4d--file-import-export-convenient-script\" style=\"display:inline-block;padding:11px 18px;background-color:#0f172a;border:1px solid #0f172a;color:#ffffff;text-decoration:none;font-weight:700;font-size:14px;border-radius:999px;margin:0 0 10px 0;\">                  Purchase Standard Version →                </a>              </td>            </tr>          </tbody>\n</table>        </div>      </td>    </tr>          <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#0b1020;padding:10px 12px;background-color:rgba(214,164,74,0.18);border:1px solid rgba(214,164,74,0.55);border-radius:12px;line-height:1.55;\">          <strong>Note:</strong> Due to Apple's policy, a Maxon license is still required on <strong>macOS</strong>. No license is required on <strong>Windows</strong>.        </div>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 12px 0;\">Support Blender Foundation</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;\">          We believe in giving back to the community that makes our work possible. Every month, we dedicate a portion of our plugin's revenue to support the Blender Foundation. Thank you for helping us contribute to the future of open-source creativity.        </div>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:18px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#64748b;line-height:1.6;\">          © 2024 Maxon Cinema 4D Import / Export Addon · blenderVfxMaster        </div>        <div style=\"padding-top:10px;\">          <a href=\"https://superhivemarket.com/products/maxon-cinema-4d--file-import-export-convenient-script\" style=\"font-size:12px;color:#0f172a;text-decoration:underline;margin-right:12px;\">            Product page          </a>          <a href=\"https://superhivemarket.com/products/maxon-cinema-4d-import-export-pro\" style=\"font-size:12px;color:#0f172a;text-decoration:underline;margin-right:12px;\">            Pro version          </a>          <a href=\"#support\" style=\"font-size:12px;color:#0f172a;text-decoration:underline;\">            Blender Foundation support          </a>        </div>      </td>    </tr>  </tbody>\n</table>\n</div>",
  "documentation": "<div style=\"width:800px;max-width:100%;margin:0 auto;padding:24px;font-family:-apple-system , BlinkMacSystemFont , 'Segoe UI' , Roboto , Helvetica , Arial , sans-serif;background-color:#ffffff;\">    <table width=\"100%\" style=\"background-color:#ffffff;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;border-radius:14px;overflow:hidden;\">        <tbody>\n<tr>      <td style=\"padding:28px 28px 22px 28px;background-color:#0b1020;background-image:linear-gradient(135deg,#0b1020 0%,#111b35 60%,#0b1020 100%);\">        <div style=\"font-size:30px;font-weight:750;color:#f8fafc;line-height:1.18;margin:0 0 10px 0;\">          📦 Plugin Documentation        </div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:rgba(248,250,252,0.86);margin:0 0 14px 0;line-height:1.75;\">          The Maxon Cinema 4D File Import-Export (.C4D File) plugin, developed by blenderVfxMaster, enables seamless integration between Blender and Cinema 4D by allowing users to import and export .c4d project files directly within Blender. This plugin eliminates the need for Cinema 4D to be installed, streamlining workflows for artists and studios working across both platforms.        </div>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Installation</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">🔧 Installation Guide</div>                <div style=\"font-size:15px;font-weight:650;color:#0f172a;margin:14px 0 6px 0;\">Download the Plugin:</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">          Obtain the .zip file from the Superhive product page.        </div>        <div style=\"font-size:15px;font-weight:650;color:#0f172a;margin:14px 0 6px 0;\">Install in Blender:</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">          <div style=\"margin-bottom:6px;\">1. Open Blender.</div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:6px;\">2. Navigate to <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;\">Edit > Preferences > Add-ons</strong>.</div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:0;\">3. Click <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;\">Install</strong>, select the downloaded .zip file, and confirm.</div>        </div>        <div style=\"font-size:15px;font-weight:650;color:#0f172a;margin:14px 0 6px 0;\">Enable the Plugin:</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0;\">          <div style=\"margin-bottom:6px;\">1. In the Add-ons list, search for <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;\">Maxon Cinema 4D File Import-Export</strong>.</div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:0;\">2. Check the box next to the plugin to activate it.</div>        </div>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Import</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">📥 Importing .c4d Files</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">          <div style=\"margin-bottom:6px;\">1. In Blender, go to <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;\">File > Import > Maxon Cinema 4D File (.c4d)</strong>.</div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:6px;\">2. Browse and select the .c4d file you wish to import.</div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:6px;\">3. In the import options, choose the asset types you want to include (e.g., models, animations, materials).</div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:8px;\">4. Click <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;\">Import Maxon Cinema 4D File</strong> to begin the import process.</div>        </div>        <div style=\"font-size:13px;color:#64748b;font-style:italic;padding:10px 12px;background-color:#f8fafc;border-left:3px solid #d6a44a;border-radius:4px;margin:0;\">          <strong>Note:</strong> Importing large .c4d files may take some time. Please be patient during the process.        </div>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Export</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">📤 Exporting .c4d Files</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">          <div style=\"margin-bottom:6px;\">1. In Blender, navigate to <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;\">File > Export > Maxon Cinema 4D File (.c4d)</strong>.</div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:6px;\">2. Choose the destination path and filename for the exported .c4d file.</div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:6px;\">3. In the export options, select the asset types you wish to include in the export.</div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:8px;\">4. Click <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;\">Export Maxon Cinema 4D File</strong> to initiate the export process.</div>        </div>        <div style=\"font-size:13px;color:#64748b;font-style:italic;padding:10px 12px;background-color:#f8fafc;border-left:3px solid #d6a44a;border-radius:4px;margin:0;\">          <strong>Note:</strong> The plugin will convert Blender assets into the .c4d format, making them compatible with Cinema 4D.        </div>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Important</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">⚠️ Important Considerations</div>        <table width=\"100%\" style=\"margin:0 0 14px 0;background-color:#fef3c7;border-radius:8px;padding:15px;border:1px solid #fbbf24;\">          <tbody>\